76561197967524117,Not Recommended,324310,32760050,Posted: 25 June,all,darshie76,"If you were thinking to get a simplified OMSI game, sadly it is not the case.The game is underwhelming on almost any single aspect. I did play Euro Truck sim for quite a while, so I was expecting a similar experience, but it is not the case. The game is neither a simulation, nor an arcade; try to do everything and end up achieving poorly.The graphics are disappointing; it looks like someone took standard assets from the Unity store and made a city out of it. The shaders for the building, the road, people, cars and trees all look different; as if someone did not even spend time trying to use the same shaders and give a consistent look. Animations of cars are quite bad, with them sliding on the road, like an early 2000 3d game. People are basically stiff and lack any sort of natural feeling. Nobody was expecting AAA graphics but at least some efforts should be put to give the game a decent look.Sounds are OK; some standard sound here and there, nothing really good or bad. The engine noise is muffled a bit; can't say if it is realistic since I rarely even take the bus.Interface is decent; simple to the point, although it is hard at times to click the right icon, since some are really big, while other are quite small. Bus customization is simple and straightforward.Driving model: it is quite horrible to be honest. As mentioned before, coming from ETS2, I was expecting something similar, due the fact that both the truck and the bus has comparable mass, although having a torsion point where the trailer goes, give a different feel to the truck. Although turning around the city is quite disappointing, since the bus feels like ""on rail""; there is no inertia, the streets are designed pretty bad; if you look at where cars stop at roadlights, you either hit them or hit something on the sidewalk (and hitting a pedestrian send your bus in the sky, before a message tell you that you did hit a pedestrian so your session is terminated). There is really a lot to do on this aspect; and if you call your game ""bus simulator"", someone would expect that you did nail the driving model for the bus; while it is not true.Traffic feels unnatural, even more than ETS2; at least cars stop when you use indicators to let you go. Cars models are really bad; there are maybe a couple of models that are decent; the rest is not that great.Lights are also disappointing; the whole map feels flat; someone did forget to turn on GI in the engine I guess. Also they look like a point, which is not really realistic (again, take out the ""simulator"" part from the name if this is what you deliver).I did play a bit trying to enjoy it, but seriously this is a disappointment in every single way. May be pleasant for a game now and then, but honestly, the driving model is so atrocious that it is impossible to play it for long sessions.Steer away, unless the game does not improve considerably."
76561197989825884,Recommended,324310,32217418,Posted: 6 June,all,Amarillon,"I'm in two minds about this game. It has massive potential and wastes almost all of it, but none the less, it is ""acceptable"" - I wouldn't rate it higher than that.The biggest problem is the limited map. If, rather than adding just DLC buses, they had optimised and expanded the routes that you can drive on, then it would have a lot more fans, a lot more mod support (Workshop is utterly wasted on this right now) and the developers would have more income to expand on it further. Unfortunately, right now, it doesn't matter how many DLC buses you buy, you're still driving the same roads in the same ""efficient"" order... or turning around and driving them the opposite way, for the same effect.It's still enjoyable if you like driving buses, but it could be so much more - and so much better optimised at times!Edited to add: I'm half tempted to change this review to ""negative"", given that they're now including all of the DLC buses with the game at the same price people paid before, but if you already own the original release, you still have to pay full price for each individual add-on. I'd be lying if I said that ddn't sting at least a little."
,Recommended,324310,24692271,"Posted: 3 August, 2016",all,Geari,"Have to say I'm quite annoyed at the number of negative reviews on this game.This is a very quality simulator, all be it with high run requirements. I have a fairly mid-high end PC, and I'm able to run it fine with no frame drops, freezing etc. As such, I will not comment any further on how the game runs, and i'll focus on the gameplay,The start of the game is a little silly, and I can imagine that the tutorial puts quite a few people off. At first I also thought that the game would be a lot more arcadey than it is (based on the tutorial).The part of the game that I love is the management side, unlike other Bus Simulation games you don't just hop into a bus and drive a pre-determined route. Sure, the actual bus might not be simulated to a high level of detail, but it has enough there to make it enjoyable and feel like a simulator.I was also very supprised to see that there is mod support...which is fantastic! I've created a custom logo for my company and imported it as a mod. I can now use it as a decal to place on my buses (Which is another great feature).One thing I noticed about this simulator, compared to other...non-super-realistic ones is that it doesnt punnish you as much. The ai traffic is fairly clever and will allow you to pull out of stops unharmed, and pedestrians will also wait before crossing the road if you're aproaching at speed.Another point on this, the ""score"" markers that appear in the bottom left, normally detailing something that you have done well, or done poorly. I was under the impression that all of these affect your star rating etc...but they don't!To give an example, my bus was diverted due to heavy traffic, and allong the diverted route a passenger requested that I stop. Upon stopping, the red marker popped up saying that I stopped at a stop that wasnt on the route. However, upon inspecting the tablet, which lists all of the factors that effect your rating it wasnt listed!All in all I find this simulator very enjoyable, which can't be said for a lot of modern simulation games. It seems as if the developers put a little bit of love into this title, which is always nice to see."
