,Recommended,324310,21690206,"Posted: 7 March, 2016",all,leburn98,"IT'S AN OMSI 2 FOR NOOBS (and that's a good thing)I was always interested in the various bus simulators, but always found the learning curve to be too steep. Games like OMSI 2 while great, are too insanely detailed for their own good, putting off someone like myself from really giving it a chance.ETS2/ATS on the otherhand proved to me that you can make a accessible simulator while keeping it just deep enough to please the hardcore. I simply wanted a bus simulator that followed the ETS2 mold and Bus Simulator 2016 is a great first step at that.PROS:- Easy to pick up and play. It comes with a nice tutorial for first timers.- The city feels alive and lived in. There are a variety of passengers (including drunk and wheel chair bound patrons).- The added business simulation element gives you incentive to continue and improve your driving skills as it directly effects your bottom line.- Ability to easily create and drive routes. A simple 5 stop route to a monster 50 stop route is possible.- You can buy and customize your buses with decals, earn extra money by placing ads, and hire drivers to drive them.- Relatively stable performance. Did not crash once (unlike a certain other game).- Supports the Thrustmaster TX 458 Italia (by customizing the controls).CONS:- No TrackIR support (the mouse is used)- Needs more optimization- No real multiplayer to speak of (driving with friends).- The AI traffic lacks other buses. It would be nice to see your competitors as well as your own buses running the same streets as it currently feels like you are the only bus driver in town.- No penalty for arriving too early for your next stop. I've finished my route as early as 8 minutes without penalty. **Perhaps this is something that is unlocked later in game?"
