76561198127572407,Recommended,324310,29291252,Posted: 15 January,all,Artful Dodger,"I cannot understand the many negative comments on this game. Im not sure what people expect from a relatively cheap, non-AAA game. Im playing on the 'test' performance version and it runs well and have not had any crashes thusfar and I get the feeling many of the earlier gripes have been attended to.PROs:+ It looks decent enough.+ The performance patch has made the game a lot better.+ Very good G27 steering wheel support, ready to play when I plugged it in.  Not even Project Cars or Assetto did that, and it took me an afternoon to set up my wheel on OMSI 2!+ Very accesible and super intuitive user interface+ Ability to run your own company, hire and fire drivers, create  lines: these add to the fun and  playability.+ Has an easy to use, uncomplicated cashier system with English speaking Passengers+ Driving is not as realistic as OMSI 2 but, it definitely is not  completely arcade. Realism is at the very worst, passable.+ Its surprisingly stable and bug free.CONS :- Single map limits the game somewhat, making it easy to burn out on the gameplay quicker than Id like.- No force feedback for engine vibration or terrain, makes the driving experience feel 'floaty'.-Workshop items are a little sparse.I think if the developers continue to work on the realism and physics of the gameplay and continue to implement suggesstions made by the community, as they have been doing, this game will hands down beat the competition.If you are looking for a starter Bus SImulator - this is the better choice. If you want an excellent, hightly realistic driving experience, but dont mind wrestling with a horribly quirky user interface,  dealing with lots of German and have the patience to figure out a hard to access, complicated routing system, get OMSI.Dont hate me, but I have been playing this as my bus simulator of choice. It may not be as realistic as it gets, but its great fun."
