76561197971692751,Not Recommended,324310,21602441,"Posted: 3 March, 2016",all,Delle(DK),"can I recommend this Bus simulator, well YES and NO.And let me start by saying that if you consider buying this or some other bus simulator then I would highly recommend you to buy bus and cable car simulator instead..Well let me review Bus simulator 16 first, it is actual quite good and have allot of good things to offer for a low price.First of all the graphics are not 2016 std. and look a bit old, though it do not matter that much since where are here to drive a bus right ? ;-)Well the city itself is create well and there is a mix of both ordinary recidential and more dence areas with sky scrapers and conventions centers, and that make it interesting to driver from a-z.The streets are filled with cars and pedestrians and sometimes even emergency vehicles that you need to let pass.It also happen that cars drive out in front of you or pedestrians almost walk on the street in front of you, so you need to keep your eyes open. Well I like these small events now and then it make the game interesting.One other things that make the game interesting is the ability to exit your seat and walk arround in the world and solve small problems. For example a drunk guy enters the bus so you have to get up and ask him to leave.And one in a while you also have to help handicapped people in/out of the bus by exit the bus and extending the ramp ;-)The all new ""run a bus business"" feature is nice, and you can even compare how well you are doing to other players though some have kind of unrealistic billion usd scores.Anyway you can also invite your friends to come and drive a trip in your bus and follow one of your routes that you create and it is kind of nice i think.It is also possible to paint your car and stick commercials on it to earn a little more, though It not really where that important to me.Well the bus driving experience is kind of okay. The feeling of sitting in the seat and driving I would say is realistic and the bus feel big ect. And you can also press various keys and sell tickets ect.The bus is also well made and in general give a good impression.However the controls of the game are not that facinating.First of all the game do not yet support Trackir ( the dev. wrote on the forum that they consider implementing it ).So many people are now forced to use the mouse to look arround or setup X and Y key on their wheel to look left and right. No matter what it is not the same as trackir and free look with the mouse. ALso I really miss the ability to look 90 degrees left and right in the bus since it is hard to see the trafic when at a T crossing and only can look 75-80 degrees left and right.Well all in all I think price level is good fair price for the product. The game is not bad, and have many nice features ( like you can hear small talk in the bus, such as boss i cant go to work today ).Also the get in and get out of the bus by passengers work pretty good, and you often fill your bus pretty good with passengers.I also like that sometimes there are events such as holliday where there are tons of passengers waiting for a ride.The game it self work in such a way you unlock features by driving from a-b.. in about 3 hour of gameplay I am level 10-11 and have unlocked the biggest bus in the game and half of the map.To unlock more I need to play the game and get xp, but I can also solve some goals ( such as having 2 bus stops in each unlocked zone ect ).All in all not a bad game but it do feel a bit like an arcade bus simulator, so I really prefer the older game named ""Bus and cablecar simulator"" since the busses are a little more realistisc, and the game experience is just a bit more fun and realistic."
